name: avocado fish tacos

food.name: pepper or hot sauce, ready to serve

instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. 

2. Finely dice onion and place in a medium bowl. Mash together with avocado. Season to taste with salt and pepper. 

3. On large baking sheet, arrange tortillas in a single layer; heat for 2 to 5 minutes. Meanwhile, coat a broiler pan with nonstick spray.

4. Crush garlic and place in a small bowl.

5. Add lime juice, hot sauce, and salt and pepper to taste, to garlic. 

6. Coat fish with mixture; arrange fillets on broiler pan.

7. Preheat broiler; broil fish, 4 inches from heat source, until cooked through, about 7 minutes.

8. Dice tomatoes and shred lettuce.

9. Spoon Avocado mixture into tortillas. Top each tortilla with fish, tomato, lettuce and cilantro.
